        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "ZF-6748 issued a patch that causes an exception to be thrown when a seek to an out-of-bounds index occurs. Unfortunately, this has caused a side-effect: calling getRow() after iterating through a rowset causes an exception, because after iterating, the value of $this->_pointer is length + 1, and getRow tries to set it back to length + 1 after seeking and fetching the row.\n\n{code}\n$table = new Zend_Db_Table($config);\n$rowset = $table->fetchAll($table->select()->limit(3)); \/\/ $rowset->_pointer is 0\nforeach($rowset as $row) {} \/\/ $rowset->_pointer is now 3\n$rowset->getRow(0); \/\/ exception\n{code}\n\nInstead of calling $this->seek($key);, getRow should just set the pointer directly:\n\n{code}\nIndex: Abstract.php\n===================================================================\n--- Abstract.php        (revision 16719)\n+++ Abstract.php        (working copy)\n@@ -394,7 +394,7 @@\n             throw new Zend_Db_Table_Rowset_Exception('No row could be found at position ' . (int) $position);\n         }\n         if ($seek == false) {\n-            $this->seek($key);\n+            $this->_pointer = $key;\n         }\n         return $row;\n     }\n{code}\n\nRegards,"
        },
